What is BigQuery and What is a Dataset?
ğŸ“Œ What is BigQuery?
BigQuery is a fully managed, serverless data warehouse provided by Google Cloud, designed for storing, querying, and analyzing large-scale data (terabytes or petabytes).

Key Features:
âœ… Massive-scale querying (optimized for TB/PB-level data)
âœ… SQL support (query data using SQL)
âœ… Serverless architecture (no infrastructure management)
âœ… Automatic scaling (computing resources are allocated dynamically)
âœ… Real-time data analysis (supports streaming data ingestion and queries)

ğŸ“Œ What is a Dataset in BigQuery?
A Dataset in BigQuery is a logical grouping used to store tables. You can think of a Dataset as a Schema (or Namespace) in a traditional database.

